```json
{
  "application": "Active Learning",
  "details": {
    "framework": "PyTorch",
    "libraries": [
      "NumPy",
      "SciPy",
      "Pandas",
      "Matplotlib",
      "TensorFlow"
    ],
    "resources": {
      "gpu": "1",
      "cpu": "1",
      "memory": "unknown",
      "storage": "unknown"
    },
    "environment": "Conda",
    "scheduler": "SLURM",
    "script_language": "Bash",
    "script_path": "~/al-ntk/experiments",
    "experiment_cases": "~/al-ntk/experiments/experiment_cases.sh",
    "results_directory": "~/results_main"
  }
}
```

This script implements an active learning algorithm using PyTorch and leverages the SLURM scheduler for resource allocation. It utilizes a conda environment for managing dependencies, employs multiple processes for parallel computation, and uses a temporary directory for storing intermediate files. The script also includes several environment variables for customizing the execution settings.
